{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"11":{"eng-name":"The Rites of Hajj (Kitab Al-Manasik Wa'l-Hajj)","ara-name":"كتاب المناسك"}},"section_detail":{"11":{"hadithnumber_first":1721,"hadithnumber_last":2045,"arabicnumber_first":1721,"arabicnumber_last":2045}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":1865,"arabicnumber":1865,"text":"حدثنا محمد بن عبيد، حدثنا حماد بن زيد، عن ايوب، عن نافع، ان ابن عمر، كان اذا قدم مكة بات بذي طوى حتى يصبح ويغتسل ثم يدخل مكة نهارا ويذكر عن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم انه فعله","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Isnaad Hasan"}],"reference":{"book":11,"hadith":145},"chapter":{"id":45,"ara-name":"باب دُخُولِ مَكَّةَ","eng-name":"Entering Makkah","isFirstHadith":true}}]}